    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="618"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d618">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1416: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wheeler</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 9, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>41. Has the Paraguayan Government answered the notes sent to you by the
                    Department’s cables of October 3?<note n="89" xml:id="d618fn89">See footnote 86
                        and footnote 87, <ref target="#pg_757">p. 757</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0873" n="759" xml:id="pg_759"/>
                <p>Department assumes from your 99, September 30, 8 p.m. and 101, October 7, 6
                        p.m.,<note n="90" xml:id="d618fn90">Neither printed.</note> that Paraguay
                    accepts to be represented at the first meeting to consider the non-aggression
                    pact on November 11.</p>
                <p>Has any indication been given regarding Paraguayan response to the suggestion of
                    the neutral representatives that forces in the Chaco be confined within the
                    limits of their respective forts? Affirmative answers to these two notes will be
                    very helpful at this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
